<br>
You say, 'Hail, Sage Xelrin'<br>
<br>
Sage Xelrin says 'Greetings Silverspell. I assume you are here to ask about my research? I imagine that word has spread of my groundbreaking approach to spell creation. Well I am always willing to enlighten those that choose to learn. As not to bog you down with too many details, my theory is simple. [Continue]'<br>
<br>
Sage Xelrin says <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>'Well the idea is rather basic. As I am sure you know, there are many magical artifacts in the world with <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>effects that we have not mastered</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. It is my conjecture that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>some of the magic may be extracted</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> from these items in order to further our magical repertoire. Even in the case where an object has a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>spell that we already have access to</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, I believe the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>binding used to tie the magic to the object could be useful as well</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> [Continue]'<br>
<br>
Sage Xelrin says 'By using this box created in cooperation with the [other sages] in Knowledge, you will be able to either extract a magical scroll or the binding used to hold the magic to the object. Those elements will be the basis for my research. Just bring anything you manage to extract for me.'<br>
<br>
You say, 'who are the other sages?'<br>
<br>
Sage Xelrin chuckles. 'Well my associates are working on their own theories for the creation of new magic. I am sure that their projects are no where near advanced as mine, but even their primitive research could prove a boon in my own work. If you happen to come across any of their research feel free to show it to my assistants, they will know the best manner in which to process it. Bring reseach from Balic to Bolcen, and Gunyth's research to Acomar. Thank you for your assistance.'<br>
____________________________________________________<br>
<br>
It looks like he wants to extract binding material from items with known effects and extract spells from items with unfamiliar effects.<br>
<br>
I think we might want to try putting Mojo Sticks from the flying poop flingers in WL into the extracter to see what it does. Or a vendor potion from a potion vendor to see if it pulls out a &quot;binding&quot;.<br>
<br>
We might need to find charged items in PoP that have PoP spell effects to extract scrolls or partial scrolls and then combine it with a binding to produce a full spell scroll.<br>
 <p><br>
Artulyn Starsummoner Arch Mage<br>
